Now, this seems to be intentional. The percpu subsystem is not explicitly tracking the physical node for each page. This means the per-node statistics are, in effect, reporting an idealized distribution of per-CPU memory, which doesn't reflect the reality of how the memory is actually used.  This can lead to significant errors in the node statistics! The fix would involve updating the `mod_node_page_state` to use `page_pgdat(page)` to track the correct physical node. This would need to be done inside the allocation loop in both `pcpu_alloc_pages` and in the error handling portion (which would need to revert the incorrect updates!).

